Basic Selenium Actions

    *   click() – Click on an element
    *   sendKeys() – Enter text in input fields
    *   getText() – Get visible text
    *   getAttribute() – Get attribute value (e.g., id, class)
    *   clear() – Clear input fields

Advanced User Interactions (Actions Class)

-   To handle more complex interactions (mouse & keyboard):

    *   moveToElement() – Move mouse to an element
    *   clickAndHold() – Click and hold
    *   doubleClick() – Double-click an element
    *   contextClick() – Right-click on an element
    *   dragAndDrop(source, target) – Drag and drop from source to target
    *   sendKeys(Keys.ENTER) – Keyboard actions
    *   release() – Release the mouse button
    *   build()	- Builds the action sequence.
    *   perform() - Performs the action sequence.


    Example of Using Actions Class

        WebElement element = driver.findElement(By.id("menu"));
        Actions actions = new Actions(driver);
        actions.moveToElement(element).click().perform();